.TH "devm_nvdimm_memremap" 9 "devm_nvdimm_memremap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_nvdimm_memremap \- map a resource that is shared across regions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" devm_nvdimm_memremap
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t offset "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that will own a reference to the shared mapping
.IP "offset" 12
physical base address of the mapping
.IP "size" 12
mapping size
.IP "flags" 12
memremap flags, or, if zero, perform an ioremap instead
